Statements made as to sentencing.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS, with credit for 6 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 18 MONTHS, same terms and conditions of probation to apply.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:  
*Serve 120 DAYS in the House of Correction (IMPOSED AND STAYED); 
*NO drugs or alcohol;
*NO new offenses;
*NO firearms;
*Cooperate with any counseling deemed appropriate by agent. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders: amount to be paid during the period of probation. If defendant is revoked, DOC shall collect up to 25% of prison funds. Remaining balance to be paid during the period of extended supervision. Any unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment. 
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
